-- Harrah's CEO expects no further takeover bids
-- 
-- Tue Dec 19, 2006 6:05pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/12/19/us-harrahs-ceo-idUSN1932130220061219

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - The chief executive of Harrah's Entertainment Inc. HET.N, which has agreed to be acquired by private equity groups Apollo Management and Texas Pacific Group TPG.UL, said on Tuesday that he does not expect further bids to emerge. 

 Harrah's on Tuesday opened up a 25-day period to pursue bids to potentially top the $90 per share offer. "I don't expect further bids, but anything is possible," CEO Gary Loveman told Reuters in an interview.